==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ruth
<hw>Ruth</hw> <pr>(r⟦udd⟧th)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Rue</er>, <pos>v.</pos>: cf. Icel. <ets>hrygg⟦edh⟧</ets>,
<ets>hryg⟦edh⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Sorrow for the misery of
another; pity; tenderness.</def> <mark>[Poetic]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧They weep
for <xex>ruth</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Chaucer.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Have
<xex>ruth</xex> of the poor.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Piers Plowman.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To stir up gentle <qex>ruth</qex>,⟦br⟧
Both for her noble blood, and for her tender youth.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which causes pity or compassion; misery;
distress; a pitiful sight.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It had been hard this <qex>ruth</qex> for to see.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With wretched miseries and woeful <qex>ruth</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruthenic</ent>⟦br⟧
